pilgrimage /ˈpɪlɡrɪmɪdʒ/

1. N-COUNT If you make a pilgrimage to a holy place, you go there for a religious reason. 朝圣 

例： ...the pilgrimage to Mecca. …前往麦加的朝圣。 

2. N-COUNT A pilgrimage is a trip that someone makes to a place that is very important to them. (去重要地方的) 出行 

例： ...a private pilgrimage to family graves. …一次对祖坟的私下参拜。

